The paper proposes a novel regularization technique for deep neural networks, which is applicable to any linear layers such as fully-connected or convolution layers. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions that the proposed method can improve the generalization performance, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories.
